         <p class="paragraph"> Crocodiles (subfamily Crocodylinae) or true crocodiles are large semiaquatic reptiles that live throughout the tropics in Africa, Asia, the Americas and Australia. Crocodylinae, all of whose members are considered true crocodiles, is classified as a biological subfamily. A broader sense of the term crocodile, Crocodylidae (which includes Tomistoma), is not used in this article. The term crocodile here applies to only the species within the subfamily of Crocodylinae. </p>
         <img class="tables" id="pic_pos2" src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/47/Crocodylus_acutus_mexico_01.jpg/330px-Crocodylus_acutus_mexico_01.jpg" width="199" height="280">
         
